        {
            "_id": "sR29kLYxvKZkQWE3",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Distort Perception",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The echopsyvne targets a creature it can see within 30 feet and alters its perception of time. The target must attempt a @Check[will|dc:40] save. Regardless of success or failure, the creature then becomes temporarily immune to this ability for 24 hours.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature perceives time to flow backward briefly and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> Time flows backward for the creature, leaving them unable to interact with the world around them. The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned]{Stunned 3}, after which it is slowed 1 for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature's mind becomes stuck in a time loop, and it becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed] by the disorienting sight for 1 minute. At the end of each of its turns, it can attempt a new Will save to reduce the remaining duration by 1 round or end it entirely on a critical success.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
